    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/16789: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-16T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 16, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>509. Embassy’s telegram No. 1238, August 14, 6 p.m. Except in strict confidence
                    to you and the Ambassador at Chungking, the assurance set forth in item 3 of
                    paragraph 1 of our telegram No. 451 of August 1, 11 a.m., has not been
                    communicated to anyone by the Department.</p>
                <p>Although the above is for your information, you may so inform the Foreign Office
                    if occasion should arise whereby you feel it would serve <pb facs="0822" n="726"
                        xml:id="pg_726"/> some useful purpose. In addition you may say that the
                    apparently complete disregard by the Japanese armed forces of the spirit if not
                    the letter of the Japanese Government’s promise is deprecated and deplored by
                    you and your Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
